1816 (8 Nov.) entire letter to Cornwall headed "Matura, Island off Ceylon", endorsed "Pr Alexander or Eclipse", rated "10/6" (deleted) and "13/6", and showing a superb strike of "ceylon/19 no 19/ 1816/packet-letter" oval datestamp (Proud Type SL1) with 9th April arrival c.d.s. on reverse. The entire letter a little worn and repaired. A very early date of use. provenance: R.G. Traill, January 1990 (Image) 	Est. $2,000-2,500

</p>
